headline.main: PRESS ACCLAIMS NEUTRALITY VOTE; Satisfaction Is Expressed Over the Country on Result, but Interpretations Vary

lead_paragraph: Editorial comments on passage of the Neutrality Amendment by the House were generally in accord in acclaiming the result. In interpretation of it the closeness of the division was variously construed as a warning to labor and as an indication of a need to bolster the national morale.
